{"title_page": "Miss International 1993", "text_new": "{{short description|Beauty pageant edition}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\n{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| winner = '''[[Agnieszka Pacha\u0142ko]]'''\n| represented = '''{{flag|Poland}}'''\n| date = October 9, 1993\n| presenters = [[Masumi Okada]]\n| image = Tokyo kosei nenkin kaikan shinjuku tokyo 2009.JPG\n| venue = Koseinenkin Kaikan Hall, [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| broadcaster = [[TV Tokyo]]\n| entrants = 47\n| debuts = [[Russia]], [[Slovak Republic]], [[Ukraine]]\n| withdraws = [[Canada]], [[Czechoslovakia]], [[Dominican Republic]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guam]], [[Iceland]], [[Italy]], [[Norway]], [[Senegal]]\n| returns = [[New Caledonia]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Portugal]]\n| before = [[Miss International 1992|1992]]\n| next = [[Miss International 1994|1994]]\n}}\n\n'''Miss International 1993''' was held on October 9, 1993 in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. [[Agnieszka Pacha\u0142ko]] earned [[Poland]]'s second Miss International crown.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Placements===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Final results\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Miss International 1993'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Poland}}''' - '''[[Agnieszka Pacha\u0142ko|Agnieszka Pachalko]]'''\n|-\n| '''1st Runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Russia}}''' - Ilmira Shamsutdinova\n|-\n| '''2nd Runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Ukraine}}''' - Nataliya Victorovna Romanenko\n|-\n| '''3rd Runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' - Kathy S\u00e1enz Herrera\n|-\n| '''4th Runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' - Mar\u00eda Cristina Arcos Torres\n|-\n| '''Semi-finalists'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Australia}}''' - Monique Ann Lysaught\n* '''{{flag|Belgium}}''' - Christelle Roelandts\n* '''{{flag|Guatemala}}''' - Diana Galv\u00e1n\n* '''{{flag|India}}''' - [[Pooja Batra]]\n* '''{{flag|Israel}}''' - [[Anat Elimelech]]\n* '''{{flag|Japan|1947}}''' - Masayo Shibasaki\n* '''{{flag|South Korea|name=Korea}}''' - Chang Eun-young\n* '''{{flag|Luxembourg}}''' - Nathalie Dos Santos\n* '''{{flag|Turkey}}''' - Hande Kazanova\n* '''{{flag|Venezuela}}''' - [[Faviola Spitale|Fabiola Spitale]]\n|}\n\n==Contestants==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* '''{{flag|Argentina}}''' - Nazarena Vanesa Gonz\u00e1lez Almada\n* '''{{flag|Australia}}''' - Monique Ann Lysaught\n* '''{{flag|Austria}}''' - Silvia Kronbichler\n* '''{{flag|Belgium}}''' - Christelle Roelandts\n* '''{{flag|Bolivia}}''' - Maria Cristina Tondelli\n* '''{{flag|Brazil}}''' - Tatiana Paula Alves\n* '''{{flag|Great Britain|name=Britain}}''' - Claire Elizabeth Smith\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' - Kathy S\u00e1enz Herrera\n* '''{{flag|Costa Rica}}''' - Laura Odio Salas\n* '''{{flag|Denmark}}''' - Mette Marie Salto\n* '''{{flag|Finland}}''' - Arlene Ulla Kaarina Kotala\n* '''{{flag|France}}''' - Marie-Ange Noelle Contart\n* '''{{flag|Germany}}''' - Katja Mordarski\n* '''{{flag|Greece}}''' - Helena Christos Zabaka\n* '''{{flag|Guatemala}}''' - Diana Galv\u00e1n\n* '''{{flag|Hawaii}}''' - Theresa Victoria Tilley\n* '''{{flag|Holland}}''' - Shirley Antoinette Bogaard\n* '''{{flag|Honduras}}''' - [[Miriam Liseth Zapata Godoy]]\n* '''{{flag|Hong Kong|colonial}}''' - Middy Yu Siu-Po\n* '''{{flag|India}}''' - [[Pooja Batra]]\n* '''{{flag|Ireland}}''' - Deborah Hannigan\n* '''{{flag|Israel}}''' - [[Anat Elimelech]]\n* '''{{flag|Japan|1947}}''' - Masayo Shibasaki\n* '''{{flag|South Korea|name=Korea}}''' - Chang Eun-young\n* '''{{flag|Luxembourg}}''' - Nathalie Dos Santos\n* '''{{flag|Malta}}''' - Melissa Joanne Portelli\n* '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' - Mar\u00eda Cristina Arcos Torres\n* '''{{flag|New Caledonia}}''' - Laure Denise Masson\n* '''{{flag|New Zealand}}''' - Monique Lorraine Joel\n* '''{{flag|Nicaragua}}''' - Ida Patricia Delaney\n* '''{{flag|Northern Mariana Islands}}''' - Tayna Castro Belyeu\n* '''{{flag|Panama}}''' - Ismenia Isabel Vel\u00e1squez\n* '''{{flag|Philippines}}''' - Sheela Mae Capili Santarin\n* '''{{flag|Poland}}''' - Agnieszka Pachalko\n* '''{{flag|Portugal}}''' - Anabela Pacheco Centeno\n* '''{{flag|Puerto Rico}}''' - Brenda Esther Robles Cort\u00e9s\n* '''{{flag|Russia}}''' - Ilmira Shamsutdinova\n* '''{{flag|Singapore}}''' - Teri Su Lian Tan\n* '''{{flag|Slovak Republic}}''' - [[Karin Majt\u00e1nov\u00e1]]\n* '''{{flag|Spain}}''' - Ana Piedad Galv\u00e1n Malag\u00f3n\n* '''{{flag|Sweden}}''' - Anna Hofvenstam\n* '''{{flag|Switzerland}}''' - Chantal Hediger\n* '''{{flag|Thailand}}''' - Supasiri Payaksiri\n* '''{{flag|Turkey}}''' - Hande Kazanova\n* '''{{flag|Ukraine}}''' - Nataliya Victorovna Romanenko\n* '''{{flag|United States}}''' - Lynette Jonene MacFee\n* '''{{flag|Venezuela}}''' - [[Faviola Spitale|Fabiola M\u00f3nica Rita Spitale Baiamonte]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n{{Miss International}}\n{{Miss International 1993 delegates}}\n\n[[Category:Miss International|1993]]\n[[Category:1993 in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:1993 beauty pageants]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Beauty pageant edition}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\n{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| winner = '''[[Agnieszka Pacha\u0142ko]]'''\n| represented = '''{{flag|Poland}}'''\n| date = October 9, 1993\n| presenters = [[Masumi Okada]]\n| image = Tokyo kosei nenkin kaikan shinjuku tokyo 2009.JPG\n| venue = Koseinenkin Kaikan Hall, [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| broadcaster = [[TV Tokyo]]\n| entrants = 47\n| debuts = [[Russia]], [[Slovak Republic]], [[Ukraine]]\n| withdraws = [[Canada]], [[Czechoslovakia]], [[Dominican Republic]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guam]], [[Iceland]], [[Italy]], [[Norway]], [[Senegal]]\n| returns = [[New Caledonia]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Portugal]]\n| before = [[Miss International 1992|1992]]\n| next = [[Miss International 1994|1994]]\n}}\n\n'''Miss International 1993''' was held on October 9, 1993 in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. [[Agnieszka Pacha\u0142ko]] earned [[Poland]]'s second Miss International crown.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Placements===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!